    authorCredentials: "Board-Certified Neurologist & Medical Director",
    category: "Education",
    content: `When you receive a laser treatment, body contouring procedure, or any device-based service at a med spa, the equipment being used matters enormously. FDA-approved devices have undergone rigorous clinical testing to demonstrate that they are both safe and effective for their intended use. Not all devices on the market meet this standard, and the difference between an FDA-approved device and an unregulated one can affect your safety, comfort, and results.

The FDA clearance process for medical aesthetic devices involves clinical trials that evaluate the device's safety profile, side effects, and treatment outcomes. Devices must demonstrate that they work as claimed and that risks are acceptable when used according to their instructions. This process can take years and cost millions of dollars, which is why some clinics cut corners by using uncleared or imported devices that have not gone through this process.

Using non-FDA-approved devices puts patients at risk in several ways. The energy levels may not be properly calibrated, leading to burns or ineffective treatments. The safety mechanisms built into approved devices may be absent. If something goes wrong, there is no regulatory body holding the manufacturer accountable. Patients may end up paying for treatments that simply do not work, or worse, that cause lasting damage.

At Rani Beauty Clinic in Renton, WA, we exclusively use FDA-approved devices and products. Our medical director, Dr. Alexander Landfield, evaluates every piece of technology in our clinic to ensure it meets the highest safety and efficacy standards. When you ask about a device at our clinic, we are happy to provide its FDA clearance information and explain exactly how it works. Your safety and results are our priority. Call (425) 539-4440 to schedule a consultation and learn about the technology behind your treatment.`,
