    authorCredentials: "Board-Certified Neurologist & Medical Director",
    category: "FAQ",
    content: `One of the most common questions patients ask before getting dermal fillers is how long the results will last. The answer varies depending on the type of filler used, the treatment area, and individual factors like your metabolism and lifestyle. At Rani Beauty Clinic in Renton, WA, we help patients set realistic expectations by explaining exactly what influences filler longevity.

Hyaluronic acid fillers, which include popular brands like Juvederm and Restylane, are the most commonly used dermal fillers. Their duration ranges from six months to over a year depending on the specific product and treatment area. Lip fillers tend to break down faster, typically lasting six to nine months, because the lips are a highly mobile area with significant blood flow. Cheek fillers and fillers placed in the nasolabial folds often last nine to twelve months or longer because these areas experience less movement. Some thicker hyaluronic acid products designed for deep volume replacement can last up to eighteen months in areas like the cheeks and jawline.

Your individual metabolism plays a significant role in how quickly fillers are absorbed. Patients with faster metabolisms, particularly those who exercise vigorously, may notice their fillers breaking down sooner. Sun exposure and lifestyle factors can also influence longevity. The skill of the injector matters as well. Properly placed filler in the correct tissue plane tends to last longer and look more natural than superficially placed product.

At Rani Beauty Clinic, our injectable treatments are overseen by Dr. Alexander Landfield, whose understanding of facial anatomy ensures precise placement for optimal longevity and aesthetics. We recommend scheduling a touch-up before your filler has fully dissolved, as maintaining a baseline can mean you need less product over time. This approach is more cost-effective and keeps your results looking consistent. Call (425) 539-4440 to schedule a filler consultation.`,
